---
import MainLayout from "../../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import MotuSidebar from '../../../components/MotuSidebar.astro';

const title = "MOTU Audio Console — UltraLite-mk3";
const description = "Control app for routing, clocking and CueMix FX.";
---

<MainLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
    <MotuSidebar />
      <div class="w-[250px] flex-shrink-0">
        <MotuSidebar />
      </div>
      <article class="prose max-w-none">
      <h1>Front Panel Console</h1>

      <h2>LCD Navigation</h2>
      <p>The UltraLite-mk3's front panel provides complete hardware control via the LCD screen and rotary encoder. This allows full setup and monitoring management without a computer.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Turn the encoder:</strong> scroll through parameter options or change a numeric value.</li>
        <li><strong>Press the encoder:</strong> select the highlighted item or confirm a value change.</li>
        <li><strong>Hold Select button:</strong> jump to the top-level menu from any sub-level.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Key LCD Parameters</h2>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Location in Menu</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Input Gain (all channels)</td><td>Inputs submenu</td><td>Adjust in 1 dB steps; shows dBFS reading</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Monitor output level</td><td>Outputs submenu</td><td>Main output to HS7 monitors</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Headphone volume</td><td>Phones</td><td>Independent of main output</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Phantom power (+48V)</td><td>Inputs → Channel 1/2</td><td>Per-channel toggle</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Sample rate</td><td>Clock submenu</td><td>Set before opening Ableton</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Clock source</td><td>Clock submenu</td><td>Internal / S/PDIF</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Hardware Mix Access (CUEMIX Mode)</h2>
      <p>Press the <strong>CUEMIX</strong> button on the front panel to switch the LCD into mixer mode. In this mode, the encoder controls the currently selected mix bus fader. Use track-select buttons (if present on the model) to navigate between mix channels and adjust levels directly on the hardware.</p>

      <h2>Saving a Hardware Snapshot</h2>
      <p>All current mix settings (levels, routings, effects parameters) are automatically stored in the MOTU's flash memory whenever you make a change in CueMix FX. When the MOTU powers up without a computer, it loads the last-saved state from flash memory — enabling reliable standalone operation with a repeatable setup every time.</p>

      <img src="https://cdn-data.motu.com/site/images/ultralite-mk3/os-support.jpg" alt="MOTU Audio Console" class="w-48 inline-block mr-4" />
    </article>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
